1
00:00:36,406 --> 00:00:37,864
Go tell Han Gyeong-wook

2
00:00:37,865 --> 00:00:38,990
FINAL EPISODE

3
00:00:38,991 --> 00:00:40,700
to get ready to pay for his crimes.

4
00:00:40,701 --> 00:00:43,286
You're awfully confident.

5
00:00:43,287 --> 00:00:46,206
Shouldn't you save that kind of talk
for after it's all over?

6
00:00:46,207 --> 00:00:47,208
Hey!

7
00:01:02,557 --> 00:01:03,558
Hey.

8
00:01:04,641 --> 00:01:05,977
You stay out of this.

9
00:01:06,769 --> 00:01:09,146
You suck. I'll finish this.

10
00:01:09,147 --> 00:01:10,481
Hey, Bulgae.

11
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:16,278
You haven't forgotten
who taught you Taekkyeon

12
00:01:16,279 --> 00:01:18,072
have you?

13
00:01:19,824 --> 00:01:22,368
You've gotten awfully chatty
since I last saw you.

14
00:01:22,994 --> 00:01:24,328
Cut the crap.

15
00:01:27,707 --> 00:01:28,958
Just bring it.

16
00:01:39,427 --> 00:01:40,428
One.

17
00:01:41,637 --> 00:01:43,722
One.

18
00:01:43,723 --> 00:01:44,724
Two.

19
00:01:46,976 --> 00:01:48,894
Two.

20
00:01:48,895 --> 00:01:50,104
One.

21
00:01:51,063 --> 00:01:52,190
Two.

22
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,902
One, two.

23
00:01:58,112 --> 00:01:59,155
One.

24
00:02:00,531 --> 00:02:01,615
Two.

25
00:02:01,616 --> 00:02:02,658
Focus.

26
00:02:03,868 --> 00:02:04,869
One.

27
00:02:06,662 --> 00:02:07,705
Two.

28
00:02:09,789 --> 00:02:10,791
One.

29
00:02:11,459 --> 00:02:12,542
Two.

30
00:02:12,543 --> 00:02:14,962
One.

31
00:02:16,589 --> 00:02:18,674
- Two.
- One.

32
00:02:43,157 --> 00:02:44,325
Comrade Major.

33
00:02:45,326 --> 00:02:47,827
Looks like your footwork
isn't what it used to be.

34
00:02:47,828 --> 00:02:49,705
You little brat.

35
00:02:57,296 --> 00:02:58,297
Comrade Major.

36
00:02:59,215 --> 00:03:00,508
Let's pull back for now.

37
00:03:07,265 --> 00:03:09,517
Hey, wait. Let them go.

38
00:03:14,063 --> 00:03:15,606
We almost had him.
You're just letting him go?

39
00:03:16,065 --> 00:03:17,316
Yeah, they just left.

40
00:03:18,442 --> 00:03:19,943
Don't lose them. Stay on them.

41
00:03:19,944 --> 00:03:21,070
Yes, got it.

42
00:03:34,125 --> 00:03:35,710
- Who was that?
- Gong-bok.

43
00:03:35,876 --> 00:03:37,628
- He's back?
- Yes.

44
00:03:38,588 --> 00:03:41,549
He says he'll decide for himself
what he needs to do.

45
00:03:42,174 --> 00:03:43,467
Then what about Beom-ryong?

46
00:03:47,263 --> 00:03:49,599
Let's deal with your nephew first.

47
00:03:50,850 --> 00:03:51,851
Nam-il!

48
00:03:54,061 --> 00:03:56,689
Nam-il, are you okay?

49
00:03:58,316 --> 00:03:59,317
Hurry.

50
00:04:03,404 --> 00:04:05,489
- Careful.
- Watch out.

51
00:04:09,619 --> 00:04:11,579
He rushed out,
saying there was a gas leak at home.

52
00:04:11,829 --> 00:04:13,663
So why are you carrying him in?

53
00:04:13,664 --> 00:04:15,206
Wait, did he actually
inhale some gas or something?

54
00:04:15,207 --> 00:04:16,458
Gas? What are you talking about?

55
00:04:16,459 --> 00:04:18,293
He probably got into trouble
and passed out.

56
00:04:19,295 --> 00:04:20,296
I'm so sorry.

57
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:24,175
But could you two
look after Nam-il for me?

58
00:04:25,051 --> 00:04:26,801
I have something urgent to do,
so I have to get going.

59
00:04:26,802 --> 00:04:28,178
Wait, you're leaving?

60
00:04:28,179 --> 00:04:30,347
Mr. Bong, I didn't think
you were like this.

61
00:04:30,348 --> 00:04:32,349
You keep disappearing
without a word these days.

62
00:04:32,350 --> 00:04:34,184
And now you're just ditching your nephew.

63
00:04:34,185 --> 00:04:36,145
How can you be so irresponsible?

64
00:04:36,812 --> 00:04:37,896
I'm sorry.

65
00:04:37,897 --> 00:04:39,940
Oh, no, Manager Bong. Wait.

66
00:04:40,608 --> 00:04:43,694
At least stay until Nam-il wakes up.

67
00:04:43,944 --> 00:04:46,364
He was so worried
when he couldn't get in touch with you.

68
00:04:46,489 --> 00:04:47,490
Manager Lee.

69
00:04:48,199 --> 00:04:52,244
Please tell Nam-il he doesn't need to
worry about me anymore.

70
00:04:52,745 --> 00:04:54,372
- What? Wait.
- What...

71
00:04:54,789 --> 00:04:55,956
Hey, wait.

72
00:04:57,041 --> 00:05:00,086
Gosh, he's acting so strange. Right?

73
00:05:00,670 --> 00:05:02,296
Something must be wrong, right?

74
00:05:10,054 --> 00:05:12,014
He's all grown up.
Why are you so worried about him?

75
00:05:13,307 --> 00:05:16,602
Grown up? Only on the outside.

76
00:05:17,812 --> 00:05:19,647
You have no idea what a kid he still is.

77
00:05:20,898 --> 00:05:22,149
That kid, Nam-il...

78
00:05:23,275 --> 00:05:25,069
He won't even eat
if there are no sausages.

79
00:05:27,154 --> 00:05:28,698
And he's such a scaredy-cat.

80
00:05:29,407 --> 00:05:32,284
He sleeps with the lights on
because he's scared of ghosts.

81
00:05:33,452 --> 00:05:35,705
And you have no idea how clumsy he is.

82
00:05:37,289 --> 00:05:40,084
He repeated a grade twice at high school,
where everyone graduates easily

83
00:05:40,793 --> 00:05:44,213
just because he miscalculated
his attendance.

84
00:05:44,755 --> 00:05:48,800
This year, I have to make sure
he finally graduates

85
00:05:48,801 --> 00:05:50,594
so he can stop being called
"the legendary repeater."

86
00:05:52,012 --> 00:05:54,056
I thought you said you were leaving
without looking back.

87
00:05:54,682 --> 00:05:56,558
You were acting all cool about it.

88
00:05:56,559 --> 00:05:58,853
I wasn't acting cool. I am cool.

89
00:06:00,062 --> 00:06:02,522
He's just being snappy
because he's a teenager

90
00:06:02,523 --> 00:06:05,985
but when he was little, he was so clingy,
always calling me uncle.

91
00:06:07,153 --> 00:06:08,570
How can I not worry about him?

92
00:06:08,571 --> 00:06:09,946
My goodness.

93
00:06:09,947 --> 00:06:11,490
So the great Bulgae

94
00:06:12,158 --> 00:06:14,118
is being swayed by his feelings.

95
00:06:18,622 --> 00:06:20,916
Are you going to crawl all night?
Step on it, will you?

96
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:23,711
- Hey, I am stepping on it.
- Well, step on it harder.

97
00:06:24,587 --> 00:06:27,298
We have to speed up if we want to catch
Han Gyeong-wook or Ri Chol Jin.

98
00:06:28,340 --> 00:06:30,092
Hey, then you drive.

99
00:06:30,468 --> 00:06:33,011
Jeez, you talk a lot
for someone hitching a ride.

100
00:06:33,012 --> 00:06:34,971
The road is wide open,
so why aren't you stepping on it?

101
00:06:34,972 --> 00:06:38,141
- Gosh, you talk way too much.
- Just step on it.

102
00:06:38,142 --> 00:06:39,143
Hey, are you going to go?

103
00:06:55,242 --> 00:06:57,744
You left so confidently.
Why did you come back?

104
00:06:57,745 --> 00:07:00,956
I had a lot on my mind back then,
but it will never happen again.

105
00:07:02,082 --> 00:07:03,626
All that matters is you came back.

106
00:07:04,418 --> 00:07:05,960
There's someone who didn't even come back.

107
00:07:05,961 --> 00:07:07,296
Hey, I'm back.

108
00:07:08,714 --> 00:07:09,840
Boss!

109
00:07:10,216 --> 00:07:12,550
I'm sorry, Gong-bok. I'm a little late.

110
00:07:12,551 --> 00:07:14,886
What? Don't tell me you brought
Hwang Hwa-san right to us.

111
00:07:14,887 --> 00:07:16,388
Darn, here we go again.

112
00:07:17,014 --> 00:07:19,933
Gang Beom-ryong, did you decide?

113
00:07:19,934 --> 00:07:21,060
Yes, I did.

114
00:07:21,852 --> 00:07:23,687
I'm the proud owner
of the Friendly Convenience Store.

115
00:07:23,854 --> 00:07:26,690
I can't stand by and watch my customers
from Yeongseon Island get beaten up.

116
00:07:27,817 --> 00:07:29,150
I'm sorry, Gong-bok.

117
00:07:29,151 --> 00:07:30,777
We won't be able
to return to the Hwasan Sect.

118
00:07:30,778 --> 00:07:33,656
Didn't I say that I'd follow you
wherever you go?

119
00:07:34,198 --> 00:07:36,242
If this is the path you've chosen

120
00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:38,118
I'll follow you without a second thought.

121
00:07:40,579 --> 00:07:41,580
I'm sorry.

122
00:07:44,792 --> 00:07:46,836
What is this, a movie scene?

123
00:07:47,086 --> 00:07:49,672
If you were going to do this anyway,
why did you storm out?

124
00:07:49,797 --> 00:07:51,674
After you guys just up and left,
our Jeong Ho...

125
00:07:53,384 --> 00:07:55,886
Do you have any idea
how upset Jeong Ho-myeong was?

126
00:07:57,513 --> 00:07:58,514
Really?

127
00:07:59,515 --> 00:08:00,807
I was about to feel hurt

128
00:08:00,808 --> 00:08:02,934
but is that really
how you felt, Mr. Jeong?

129
00:08:02,935 --> 00:08:04,519
That's just...

130
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,272
I was just worried
the operation would get screwed up.

131
00:08:07,022 --> 00:08:08,606
Anyway, since things turned out this way

132
00:08:08,607 --> 00:08:10,817
I'm going to stop Han Gyeong-wook
as well as your boss.

133
00:08:10,818 --> 00:08:12,110
So don't give me any trouble from now on.

134
00:08:12,111 --> 00:08:15,363
Right. I have to stop our boss
from taking the wrong path.

135
00:08:15,364 --> 00:08:16,990
What do we do first?

136
00:08:16,991 --> 00:08:19,909
Should we take out the spies
he was tailing?

137
00:08:19,910 --> 00:08:23,621
They're holed up in a tourist hotel
on the outskirts of Yeongseon Island.

138
00:08:23,622 --> 00:08:25,916
Perfect. Now that our heavy hitter is here

139
00:08:26,166 --> 00:08:27,250
should we go now?

140
00:08:27,251 --> 00:08:28,377
- Let's go.
- No.

141
00:08:29,128 --> 00:08:30,504
The election is right around the corner.

142
00:08:31,171 --> 00:08:33,465
Even if we take care of Ri Chol Jin

143
00:08:33,631 --> 00:08:36,176
if Han Gyeong-wook gets elected,
it's all over.

144
00:08:36,927 --> 00:08:39,554
And we have no idea when the code
for the package will be cracked.

145
00:08:39,804 --> 00:08:42,308
We have to make a bold move
before it's too late.

146
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,767
A bold move?

147
00:08:44,226 --> 00:08:46,562
You need bait to catch a big fish.

148
00:08:49,773 --> 00:08:53,861
We're going to catch Han Gyeong-wook
with Ri Chol Jin as bait.

149
00:08:54,945 --> 00:08:56,571
Use Ri Chol Jin as bait?

150
00:08:56,572 --> 00:08:58,824
I've already called for backup to help us.

151
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:04,121
YEONGSEON FERRY TERMINAL

152
00:09:04,246 --> 00:09:06,415
TEMPORARY PICK-UP AND DROP-OFF ZONE

153
00:09:06,707 --> 00:09:09,125
Yes, don't worry.
We're tracking her closely.

154
00:09:09,126 --> 00:09:12,254
I approved Prosecutor Gang's leave
on purpose.

155
00:09:12,922 --> 00:09:16,258
You know things got out of hand last time
because you lost her, right?

156
00:09:17,009 --> 00:09:18,509
This time, you're not tailing her.

157
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,929
You're eliminating her.

158
00:09:21,931 --> 00:09:23,474
You absolutely cannot make any mistakes.

159
00:09:23,682 --> 00:09:25,517
Yes, we'll get it right
this time for sure.

160
00:09:26,143 --> 00:09:27,227
Yes, sir.

161
00:09:29,939 --> 00:09:31,982
That old geezer is really on our case.

162
00:09:32,566 --> 00:09:33,650
This is so annoying.

163
00:09:33,651 --> 00:09:36,277
But can we really eliminate a prosecutor?

164
00:09:36,278 --> 00:09:37,988
Won't that cause some kind of problem?

165
00:09:38,447 --> 00:09:39,864
What's the problem?

166
00:09:39,865 --> 00:09:41,909
The Chief Prosecutor
of the Criminal Division has our back.

167
00:09:43,118 --> 00:09:45,913
Stop the useless worrying
and let's get this right for once.

168
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,082
I'm so sick and tired
of tailing Prosecutor Gang.

169
00:09:51,210 --> 00:09:52,794
Hey, she got in. Let's go!

170
00:09:52,795 --> 00:09:55,213
All right, let's go.

171
00:09:55,214 --> 00:09:57,257
Where is she off to this time?

172
00:09:59,009 --> 00:10:00,551
Gosh! What the hell?

173
00:10:00,552 --> 00:10:01,595
- What?
- What is it?

174
00:10:02,179 --> 00:10:03,305
This is strange.

175
00:10:03,681 --> 00:10:05,683
- What? Did something burst?
- Hey, over here.

176
00:10:06,266 --> 00:10:08,851
- What? What's wrong with it?
- Darn it.

177
00:10:08,852 --> 00:10:10,646
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

178
00:10:11,230 --> 00:10:13,940
Hey, Prosecutor Gang is leaving!
Do something!

179
00:10:13,941 --> 00:10:15,650
- It's completely flat.
- Darn it!

180
00:10:15,651 --> 00:10:17,319
The old geezer is going to flip out again.

181
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:20,656
This is our first time meeting in person,
but strangely, it doesn't feel awkward.

182
00:10:21,824 --> 00:10:24,118
Maybe because
you've helped me out a few times.

183
00:10:24,284 --> 00:10:26,911
Well, I wouldn't go so far
as to say I helped you.

184
00:10:26,912 --> 00:10:28,831
All I did was use a few minor tricks.

185
00:10:29,748 --> 00:10:32,251
I'd say your skills are too great
to be called "minor tricks."

186
00:10:33,002 --> 00:10:37,756
I mean, you helped me shake off
those relentless guys several times.

187
00:10:38,924 --> 00:10:40,091
Thank you for that.

188
00:10:40,092 --> 00:10:42,177
You can save your thanks for later.

189
00:10:43,095 --> 00:10:46,807
I'm afraid I have
a difficult request to ask of you.

190
00:10:47,516 --> 00:10:48,808
- A difficult request?
- Yes.

191
00:10:48,809 --> 00:10:51,394
- I'm so excited. What is it?
- You'll see when we get there.

192
00:10:51,395 --> 00:10:53,022
Everyone is waiting for you.

193
00:11:17,463 --> 00:11:18,714
Prosecutor Gang.

194
00:11:20,758 --> 00:11:21,884
Have you been well, Je-sun?

195
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:32,226
Well, as you've all heard,
the situation isn't good right now.

196
00:11:32,227 --> 00:11:34,062
North Korean agents have come south

197
00:11:34,063 --> 00:11:36,522
and with Hwang Hwa-san
joining Heaven Capital

198
00:11:36,523 --> 00:11:38,192
the development is picking up speed.

199
00:11:38,484 --> 00:11:40,151
The victims of Heaven Capital's
collection practices

200
00:11:40,152 --> 00:11:42,821
are preparing to protest in response.

201
00:11:43,906 --> 00:11:45,031
The worst part is--

202
00:11:45,032 --> 00:11:47,784
We don't know when the password
for the package will be cracked.

203
00:11:47,785 --> 00:11:48,827
That's right.

204
00:11:49,411 --> 00:11:51,579
While we wait
for the package's password to be cracked

205
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:53,289
we can't just sit on our hands.

206
00:11:53,290 --> 00:11:56,668
We need to find another way
before Han Gyeong-wook gets elected.

207
00:11:59,213 --> 00:12:02,633
Prosecutor Gang, by any chance,
are you still being tailed?

208
00:12:03,217 --> 00:12:07,387
Yes, detectives are sticking to me
like leeches wherever I go

209
00:12:07,805 --> 00:12:09,723
so it's not as easy
to move around as I'd hoped.

210
00:12:09,890 --> 00:12:10,973
Hey, Ho-myeong.

211
00:12:10,974 --> 00:12:13,101
If even the Prosecutor
can't move around freely

212
00:12:13,102 --> 00:12:16,230
do you think we can really catch
Han Gyeong-wook using Ri Chol Jin?

213
00:12:16,355 --> 00:12:19,858
If you're planning
to expose their partnership, forget it.

214
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:22,485
- Why?
- Ri Chol Jin and the other agents

215
00:12:22,486 --> 00:12:27,156
would have created fake identities
with no relatives or connections.

216
00:12:27,157 --> 00:12:28,366
Even if we catch them

217
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:30,451
it will take months
just to confirm their identities.

218
00:12:30,452 --> 00:12:32,121
The game will be over by then.

219
00:12:33,163 --> 00:12:36,750
Unless they go around advertising,
"I'm a spy,"

220
00:12:37,126 --> 00:12:38,836
it's impossible to use Ri Chol Jin.

221
00:12:39,586 --> 00:12:40,795
You seem to know a lot about that.

222
00:12:40,796 --> 00:12:41,880
Well, that's because I...

223
00:12:46,969 --> 00:12:48,928
What Je-sun says is right.

224
00:12:48,929 --> 00:12:50,805
Even if we do catch Ri Chol Jin

225
00:12:50,806 --> 00:12:53,559
it's meaningless if we can't connect him
to Han Gyeong-wook.

226
00:12:53,725 --> 00:12:55,310
Then we'll have to find a way
to make it meaningful.

227
00:12:56,478 --> 00:12:58,146
- Gong-bok.
- Yes.

228
00:12:58,147 --> 00:13:02,359
Confirm the location of the detectives
tailing Prosecutor Gang with CCTV footage.

229
00:13:03,235 --> 00:13:04,486
Okay. I will.

230
00:13:05,362 --> 00:13:08,949
Prosecutor Gang.
Do you happen to know any reporters?

231
00:13:09,408 --> 00:13:12,995
Someone who can work as fast as possible
and write an article with a huge impact.

232
00:13:13,162 --> 00:13:14,621
A huge impact...

233
00:13:16,206 --> 00:13:17,416
Does it have to be a reporter?

234
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:21,170
Well, not really, as long as
they can grab the public's attention.

235
00:13:21,628 --> 00:13:22,753
How about a million-subscriber
content-creator?

236
00:13:22,754 --> 00:13:24,131
A million-subscribers?

237
00:13:24,965 --> 00:13:26,049
That's perfect.

238
00:13:27,634 --> 00:13:30,429
All right, everyone. Listen up.

239
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:31,680
Starting now

240
00:13:32,181 --> 00:13:33,765
we're going to use Ri Chol Jin

241
00:13:34,016 --> 00:13:36,476
to link Hwang Hwa-san, Chairman Do,
and Han Gyeong-wook.

242
00:13:36,810 --> 00:13:38,312
And once they're all connected

243
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,065
we're taking them all down in one shot.

244
00:13:45,694 --> 00:13:46,862
Je-sun.

245
00:13:48,363 --> 00:13:49,531
Prosecutor Gang.

246
00:13:50,199 --> 00:13:52,576
I heard you got all your memories back.

247
00:13:54,453 --> 00:13:56,538
Just as I suspected,
you're no ordinary person.

248
00:13:58,415 --> 00:14:00,167
I thought you would've called me.

249
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,921
Are you okay?

250
00:14:06,882 --> 00:14:08,091
Prosecutor Gang.

251
00:14:13,138 --> 00:14:14,723
You should stop right now.

252
00:14:15,766 --> 00:14:16,934
Stop what?

253
00:14:17,351 --> 00:14:18,518
Having feelings for me.

254
00:14:19,853 --> 00:14:20,854
Excuse me?

255
00:14:21,772 --> 00:14:24,858
I understand. A person's heart...

256
00:14:25,234 --> 00:14:27,569
I know it doesn't always do what you want.

257
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,530
And on top of that, I am quite...

258
00:14:32,074 --> 00:14:33,075
Yes, well.

259
00:14:33,784 --> 00:14:37,579
I know it won't be easy to move on,
but you must get a hold of yourself.

260
00:14:38,830 --> 00:14:41,708
Are you saying
that I have a crush on you, Je-sun?

261
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:46,421
Unbelievable.

262
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:19,997
According to Sergeant Kim

263
00:15:20,622 --> 00:15:23,749
once the protest begins,
Heaven Capital will force their way in.

264
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:26,253
Regardless of whether people get hurt.

265
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:29,839
The protest is tomorrow.
Isn't there any way to stop it?

266
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:32,134
What's the point of stopping them?

267
00:15:32,759 --> 00:15:34,552
Let's just grab some signs and fight them.

268
00:15:34,553 --> 00:15:37,138
Are you crazy?
They're not for hitting people.

269
00:15:37,139 --> 00:15:40,391
I'm sick of all this.
I just want to go back to the restaurant.

270
00:15:40,392 --> 00:15:43,185
Me too. It's been so long
since I've used my wok

271
00:15:43,186 --> 00:15:44,604
that my hands are getting stiff.

272
00:15:45,897 --> 00:15:47,565
Forget the protest.

273
00:15:47,566 --> 00:15:50,860
Can't we just go back to the restaurant
and reopen?

274
00:15:50,861 --> 00:15:52,654
- Dad!
- Come on.

275
00:15:53,488 --> 00:15:54,989
Our neighbors are going to get hurt.

276
00:15:54,990 --> 00:15:57,742
We can't just stand by and do nothing.

277
00:15:57,743 --> 00:16:00,244
What else can we do besides watch?

278
00:16:00,245 --> 00:16:03,623
There's no time, and there's nothing
we can do on our own.

279
00:16:03,999 --> 00:16:06,000
Honestly, isn't it all over?

280
00:16:06,001 --> 00:16:07,252
There is a way.

281
00:16:08,253 --> 00:16:09,503
- Prosecutor Gang.
- Prosecutor Gang.

282
00:16:09,504 --> 00:16:10,880
It's been a while.

283
00:16:10,881 --> 00:16:12,007
Hello, everyone.

284
00:16:12,758 --> 00:16:16,093
Before the protest happens,
there's a way to stop Han Gyeong-wook

285
00:16:16,094 --> 00:16:17,846
and the Heaven Capital goons
in their tracks.

286
00:16:18,347 --> 00:16:20,390
So, will you help me?

287
00:16:27,022 --> 00:16:31,568
MOTEL

288
00:16:41,286 --> 00:16:44,413
The prosecutor has already
taken care of the hotel

289
00:16:44,414 --> 00:16:48,292
so don't be nervous
and just play your parts.

290
00:16:48,293 --> 00:16:49,586
- Yes.
- Understood.

291
00:16:50,670 --> 00:16:51,754
- Don't be nervous.
- Right.

292
00:16:51,755 --> 00:16:53,964
Right, let's get to our positions.

293
00:16:53,965 --> 00:16:55,008
Right, let's go.

294
00:17:06,685 --> 00:17:08,646
Where are you?

295
00:17:14,903 --> 00:17:16,405
There you are.

296
00:17:22,618 --> 00:17:24,204
Prosecutor Gang. I found them.

297
00:17:24,746 --> 00:17:27,332
The detectives are
at Yeongseon Intersection.

298
00:17:30,961 --> 00:17:33,505
This is like trying to find
a needle in a haystack.

299
00:17:34,673 --> 00:17:36,216
Let's just give up.

300
00:17:37,551 --> 00:17:39,094
And report that we lost her again?

301
00:17:39,594 --> 00:17:43,014
If we do, we're both getting the ax
for real this time.

302
00:17:43,765 --> 00:17:46,392
Stop whining and just keep looking.
We've been at this all day.

303
00:17:46,393 --> 00:17:48,644
It's not like Prosecutor Gang
will just magically appear...

304
00:17:48,645 --> 00:17:49,937
She has appeared.

305
00:17:49,938 --> 00:17:51,230
- Where?
- Over there!

306
00:17:51,231 --> 00:17:53,274
The convenience store. See?

307
00:17:53,275 --> 00:17:55,401
There she is! Yes! We got her!

308
00:17:55,402 --> 00:17:56,694
I told you she'd be around here!

309
00:17:56,695 --> 00:17:57,903
We got her!

310
00:17:57,904 --> 00:17:59,656
She got in.

311
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:04,368
I've got you now.

312
00:18:04,369 --> 00:18:05,620
Is she going this way? No, that way!

313
00:18:06,246 --> 00:18:08,497
What's the status on securing the package?

314
00:18:08,498 --> 00:18:09,957
It's proceeding smoothly.

315
00:18:09,958 --> 00:18:11,459
We're running out of time.

316
00:18:11,460 --> 00:18:13,169
The election is right around the corner.

317
00:18:13,170 --> 00:18:14,253
I'm sure you're aware of that.

318
00:18:14,254 --> 00:18:16,172
Didn't I tell you it's in progress?

319
00:18:16,173 --> 00:18:17,298
If it's proving too difficult

320
00:18:17,299 --> 00:18:19,759
try asking Hwang Hwa-san
and Chairman Do for help.

321
00:18:22,345 --> 00:18:25,807
You still don't know
what those punks are scheming, do you?

322
00:18:25,932 --> 00:18:27,224
What do you mean by that?

323
00:18:27,225 --> 00:18:30,770
I had a bad feeling about those two,
so I did some digging.

324
00:18:31,146 --> 00:18:33,981
I'll send you the data,
so you can see for yourself and decide.

325
00:18:33,982 --> 00:18:36,860
And I'll take care of the package myself

326
00:18:37,277 --> 00:18:39,237
so stop pestering me. Understood?

327
00:18:43,825 --> 00:18:46,661
There are so many of you,
and you can't even take down two guys?

328
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,663
Pull yourselves together. Now.

329
00:18:48,788 --> 00:18:51,415
We have to retrieve the package
before Deputy Director Han finds out.

330
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:52,417
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

331
00:19:14,439 --> 00:19:16,774
Oh, my. I'm so sorry, sir.

332
00:19:16,775 --> 00:19:20,861
The room below is complaining about
water leaking from the ceiling.

333
00:19:20,862 --> 00:19:23,322
May I take a quick look at the bathroom?

334
00:19:23,323 --> 00:19:25,200
Wait, why is it leaking?

335
00:19:25,408 --> 00:19:26,992
Then just move them to another room.

336
00:19:26,993 --> 00:19:31,288
But a large group just checked in.
We're completely full.

337
00:19:31,289 --> 00:19:32,457
This won't take long.

338
00:19:34,417 --> 00:19:37,002
Will it really be quick?

339
00:19:37,003 --> 00:19:38,463
Of course.

340
00:19:38,588 --> 00:19:40,839
Mr. Jo from the hardware store here
is a total professional.

341
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:41,841
Mr. Jo.

342
00:19:44,511 --> 00:19:47,013
It'll just take three minutes.

343
00:19:47,597 --> 00:19:49,891
Making a scene won't do us any good.
Finish it up quickly.

344
00:19:51,351 --> 00:19:53,978
Then you have to be quick.

345
00:19:53,979 --> 00:19:55,730
Sure. Three minutes.

346
00:19:56,481 --> 00:19:58,524
Yes. Thank you.

347
00:19:58,525 --> 00:20:00,693
We'll give you
a late checkout when you leave.

348
00:20:00,694 --> 00:20:03,196
Thank you.

349
00:20:13,832 --> 00:20:14,916
Thank you.

350
00:20:20,964 --> 00:20:23,674
Gosh, she's picked
the perfect spot to die.

351
00:20:23,675 --> 00:20:26,011
Let's go before we lose her again.

352
00:20:26,303 --> 00:20:27,929
Let's go.

353
00:20:38,565 --> 00:20:39,649
This way, right?

354
00:20:49,326 --> 00:20:50,869
Hey, who are those guys?

355
00:20:54,497 --> 00:20:56,124
- Why are they here?
- What's going on?

356
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:58,752
What is this?

357
00:20:59,878 --> 00:21:01,545
Yes, what is it?

358
00:21:01,546 --> 00:21:02,838
Excuse me.

359
00:21:02,839 --> 00:21:05,424
You're the detectives from Imcheon Station
for backup, right?

360
00:21:05,425 --> 00:21:06,508
Backup?

361
00:21:06,509 --> 00:21:09,345
Yes, a report came in about
armed communists holding hostages here.

362
00:21:09,346 --> 00:21:10,472
Aren't you here as backup?

363
00:21:11,097 --> 00:21:12,348
- Armed communists?
- Yes.

364
00:21:12,349 --> 00:21:14,433
This is an emergency. We don't have time.
Hurry, get out of the car.

365
00:21:14,434 --> 00:21:17,812
- Hold on. All right.
- Hurry.

366
00:21:23,526 --> 00:21:26,613
Okay, everyone.
Don't be scared, all right?

367
00:21:26,905 --> 00:21:28,823
- You can do this, right?
- I have to.

368
00:21:29,074 --> 00:21:31,368
- To get my house back without protest.
- Right.

369
00:21:34,663 --> 00:21:36,580
That's right. Listen.

370
00:21:36,581 --> 00:21:39,000
Float like a butterfly, sting like a bee!

371
00:21:40,293 --> 00:21:42,378
It's been a while.
Should I warm up a little?

372
00:21:42,379 --> 00:21:43,463
Don't be nervous.

373
00:21:43,963 --> 00:21:46,091
You seem nervous.

374
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:49,010
- All right, come on out.
- Hey, wait a minute.

375
00:21:50,428 --> 00:21:52,096
Yes, we did come here as backup, but...

376
00:21:52,097 --> 00:21:54,556
- Gosh, careful.
- Hey, sorry about that.

377
00:21:54,557 --> 00:21:56,559
Be careful.
The situation looks pretty bad.

378
00:21:57,686 --> 00:22:00,479
Wait, but will this actually
get a lot of views?

379
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:03,273
Do you know what's important
for getting views?

380
00:22:03,274 --> 00:22:05,859
- What?
- It's all about clickbait.

381
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:08,529
My views have been down lately

382
00:22:08,530 --> 00:22:12,533
so I was wondering
if I should break another arm.

383
00:22:12,534 --> 00:22:15,285
If there's a real spy here,
this will break ten million views.

384
00:22:15,286 --> 00:22:16,453
Man, ten million.

385
00:22:16,454 --> 00:22:18,497
- It'd be amazing to pass ten million.
- Okay, I'm going live.

386
00:22:18,498 --> 00:22:20,417
- Okay.
- We're on.

387
00:22:22,043 --> 00:22:24,796
Hello, everyone. This is Sweatzilla.

388
00:22:25,004 --> 00:22:27,172
Hey, my Fluffys! Hope you're doing well.

389
00:22:27,173 --> 00:22:29,133
Today is a very important day.

390
00:22:29,134 --> 00:22:32,219
In this day and age,
do spies exist or not?

391
00:22:32,220 --> 00:22:34,054
Oh, they do. Right here.

392
00:22:34,055 --> 00:22:36,890
Yes, today I got a tip that
armed communists are holding out here

393
00:22:36,891 --> 00:22:38,435
so I've come to the scene.

394
00:22:38,935 --> 00:22:41,354
"Stop lying"? I'm serious here.

395
00:22:41,563 --> 00:22:45,357
I'm telling you, I got an emergency tip
and came right here.

396
00:22:45,358 --> 00:22:46,443
Hold on.

397
00:22:47,193 --> 00:22:49,988
Look at this.
The cops are all over the place.

398
00:22:59,247 --> 00:23:00,790
I wonder where the leak is.

399
00:23:04,878 --> 00:23:07,421
- Over there.
- Where?

400
00:23:07,422 --> 00:23:08,840
Someone's hurt!

401
00:23:09,591 --> 00:23:11,175
What are we going to do?

402
00:23:11,176 --> 00:23:12,634
Oh, this is bad. My goodness.

403
00:23:12,635 --> 00:23:14,386
- Oh, no. What do we do?
- My gosh.

404
00:23:14,387 --> 00:23:17,473
- Chairman.
- Look. It's blood.

405
00:23:17,474 --> 00:23:18,683
- Look!
- Blood!

406
00:23:21,269 --> 00:23:24,855
The armed communists in there
are hurting people...

407
00:23:24,856 --> 00:23:28,234
Looks like those scumbags
are running wild in there.

408
00:23:30,612 --> 00:23:32,614
It would be too dangerous
to go in recklessly.

409
00:23:33,072 --> 00:23:34,156
- Detectives.
- Yes?

410
00:23:34,157 --> 00:23:35,784
You've handled negotiations before, right?

411
00:23:36,159 --> 00:23:37,242
- Negotiations?
- Negotiations?

412
00:23:37,243 --> 00:23:39,871
You detectives are the only ones
I can trust here.

413
00:23:40,497 --> 00:23:42,581
- Please take command of the scene.
- Us? We...

414
00:23:42,582 --> 00:23:45,793
Hey! Give the detectives here
the megaphone!

415
00:23:45,794 --> 00:23:48,754
- The megaphone.
- Quick, to the hospital!

416
00:23:48,755 --> 00:23:50,088
- It hurts.
- Hospital!

417
00:23:50,089 --> 00:23:51,465
Are you all right, sir?

418
00:23:51,466 --> 00:23:52,549
Here you go.

419
00:23:52,550 --> 00:23:54,719
The megaphone!

420
00:23:55,094 --> 00:23:56,095
Sir!

421
00:23:57,555 --> 00:24:00,308
There are armed communists!

422
00:24:02,060 --> 00:24:04,604
Listen up, armed communists!

423
00:24:05,522 --> 00:24:09,192
You are completely surrounded!

424
00:24:09,943 --> 00:24:11,902
Drop your weapons right now!

425
00:24:11,903 --> 00:24:14,113
- Comrade Major!
- Surrender!

426
00:24:15,782 --> 00:24:17,534
I'll say it again!

427
00:24:18,117 --> 00:24:19,786
Listen up, armed communists!

428
00:24:20,912 --> 00:24:23,915
Drop your weapons and surrender!

429
00:24:24,541 --> 00:24:28,168
Then we'll spare your lives!

430
00:24:28,169 --> 00:24:29,295
Armed communists?

431
00:24:29,879 --> 00:24:31,129
Are they talking about us?

432
00:24:31,130 --> 00:24:33,550
- We have no intention to harm you!
- I don't know.

433
00:24:34,217 --> 00:24:36,719
- Not at all!
- Get ready. Let's hide first.

434
00:24:38,388 --> 00:24:39,639
Freeze!

435
00:24:41,015 --> 00:24:42,559
If a single one of you moves

436
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:44,894
I'm throwing this.

437
00:24:55,488 --> 00:24:58,783
- This little scumbag.
- I'm going to throw it. I really will!

438
00:25:00,118 --> 00:25:01,995
- Who on earth are you?
- Me?

439
00:25:02,829 --> 00:25:04,706
Team Leader Jo Seong-won
of the Anti-Communist Investigation Team.

440
00:25:05,290 --> 00:25:07,374
A spy hunter who catches spies like you.

441
00:25:07,375 --> 00:25:09,460
And I've caught a lot of them.

442
00:25:10,211 --> 00:25:11,296
I see.

443
00:25:12,338 --> 00:25:14,923
That punk who was after the package
ten years ago?

444
00:25:14,924 --> 00:25:16,968
That's right, Major Ri Chol Jin.

445
00:25:17,677 --> 00:25:20,387
Give up. You're not getting out of here.

446
00:25:20,388 --> 00:25:22,264
Because I told everyone
there were armed communists here.

447
00:25:22,265 --> 00:25:23,765
So what do you think the media will do?

448
00:25:23,766 --> 00:25:25,184
They'll go crazy, won't they?

449
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:28,937
Right?

450
00:25:28,938 --> 00:25:30,439
You have two choices.

451
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:31,441
First...

452
00:25:32,317 --> 00:25:33,525
Turn yourselves in and find salvation.

453
00:25:33,526 --> 00:25:34,651
Second...

454
00:25:34,652 --> 00:25:36,904
Get dragged out by the military
and police like dogs.

455
00:25:36,905 --> 00:25:39,781
Think about it.
Which option is better for you?

456
00:25:39,782 --> 00:25:40,909
Choose.

457
00:25:55,548 --> 00:25:57,466
- Oh, hello!
- Oh, no.

458
00:25:57,467 --> 00:26:00,135
Just a moment! Come over here.

459
00:26:00,136 --> 00:26:04,514
These are the heroes
who captured the spies on their own.

460
00:26:04,515 --> 00:26:07,100
- Let's have a round of applause!
- Applause!

461
00:26:07,101 --> 00:26:09,102
The comments are going wild.

462
00:26:09,103 --> 00:26:10,771
- Please say hi!
- Hello.

463
00:26:10,772 --> 00:26:13,982
- Fluffys!
- All right, that's enough.

464
00:26:13,983 --> 00:26:17,277
- Okay, stop filming.
- Yes, great work!

465
00:26:17,278 --> 00:26:19,279
- Gosh, it's so chaotic.
- Let's go.

466
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:21,240
- You've worked hard.
- Gosh! You scared me!

467
00:26:21,532 --> 00:26:23,159
It's amazing how you caught those spies.

468
00:26:23,743 --> 00:26:26,829
Looks like following me around
has finally paid off.

469
00:26:28,957 --> 00:26:30,040
How did it go?

470
00:26:30,041 --> 00:26:31,292
It went according to plan.

471
00:26:31,459 --> 00:26:33,211
As soon as we get Ri Chol Jin's confession

472
00:26:33,878 --> 00:26:38,049
I'll request arrest warrants
for all of Han Gyeong-wook's people.

473
00:26:38,758 --> 00:26:42,344
Getting them issued won't be easy,
but we need to take drastic measures.

474
00:26:42,345 --> 00:26:46,765
Then as soon as you bring the warrants,
we'll be ready to make the arrests.

475
00:26:46,766 --> 00:26:48,559
We'll gather all of them in one place.

476
00:26:49,227 --> 00:26:51,019
Be here by 6:00 p.m. tomorrow

477
00:26:51,020 --> 00:26:53,982
with the warrants and all your personnel.

478
00:26:54,399 --> 00:26:58,277
But will it really be possible
to lure Han Gyeong-wook right on time?

479
00:26:58,945 --> 00:27:02,197
The election is the day after
the Yeongseon Island rally.

480
00:27:02,198 --> 00:27:05,618
Tomorrow is our only chance
to lure and catch Han Gyeong-wook.

481
00:27:06,369 --> 00:27:08,870
I'll find a way to lure him in

482
00:27:08,871 --> 00:27:11,666
so you just be thoroughly prepared,
Prosecutor Gang.

483
00:27:12,542 --> 00:27:13,543
Okay.

484
00:27:18,881 --> 00:27:20,049
So, Prosecutor Gang...

485
00:27:21,676 --> 00:27:23,219
caught Ri Chol Jin?

486
00:27:24,095 --> 00:27:25,178
Yes.

487
00:27:25,179 --> 00:27:27,347
Since it's drawn this much attention

488
00:27:27,348 --> 00:27:30,226
Ri Chol Jin knows very well
that it's too late to back out.

489
00:27:30,935 --> 00:27:32,811
If he wants to live,
he'll confess to something.

490
00:27:32,812 --> 00:27:35,439
All right, let's say it's all gone
according to your plan so far.

491
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,606
What's next?

492
00:27:36,607 --> 00:27:38,275
You're planning to arrest Han, Chairman Do

493
00:27:38,276 --> 00:27:40,485
and even our boss at the same time.

494
00:27:40,486 --> 00:27:41,529
You think that's even possible?

495
00:27:42,030 --> 00:27:44,657
If we use the package as bait,
it's totally possible.

496
00:27:45,825 --> 00:27:47,367
Now that Ri Chol Jin's been caught

497
00:27:47,368 --> 00:27:49,494
it would be a fatal blow
if the package got out.

498
00:27:49,495 --> 00:27:51,455
Han Gyeong-wook
will have no choice but to come.

499
00:27:51,456 --> 00:27:54,666
And Hwang Hwa-san will need the package
to take on Han Gyeong-wook.

500
00:27:54,667 --> 00:27:59,087
But do we really have to gather them all
and catch them at once?

501
00:27:59,088 --> 00:28:01,423
If we miss even one of them,
the Yeongseon Island project

502
00:28:01,424 --> 00:28:03,216
could still go through.

503
00:28:03,217 --> 00:28:06,429
We have to strike all at once
before they get suspicious.

504
00:28:07,722 --> 00:28:09,639
I know, but still, it's a little...

505
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,725
Why? Is there a problem?

506
00:28:11,726 --> 00:28:15,103
What happens if Prosecutor Gang
doesn't make it in time?

507
00:28:15,104 --> 00:28:16,731
We'd have to hold them off ourselves.

508
00:28:17,356 --> 00:28:18,524
Is that possible?

509
00:28:24,072 --> 00:28:26,908
It isn't.

510
00:28:28,785 --> 00:28:29,911
What?

511
00:28:30,244 --> 00:28:31,954
Until Prosecutor Gang arrives

512
00:28:32,455 --> 00:28:34,415
we have to stall for as long as possible.

513
00:28:39,629 --> 00:28:41,297
We'll use guerrilla tactics.

514
00:28:58,856 --> 00:28:59,857
Why aren't you sleeping?

515
00:29:05,822 --> 00:29:07,907
It's tomorrow. How could I sleep?

516
00:29:14,288 --> 00:29:15,289
You're awake too?

517
00:29:16,374 --> 00:29:18,835
What? You're all here?

518
00:29:19,669 --> 00:29:20,795
Where's Gong-bok?

519
00:29:21,462 --> 00:29:23,046
He conked out a while ago.

520
00:29:23,047 --> 00:29:24,214
Gosh.

521
00:29:24,215 --> 00:29:27,343
He's the biggest worrier of all,
but he sleeps like a log.

522
00:29:28,219 --> 00:29:30,138
He should get some sleep while he can.

523
00:29:30,263 --> 00:29:31,764
We don't know
what's going to happen tomorrow.

524
00:29:38,062 --> 00:29:39,480
Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong.

525
00:29:40,189 --> 00:29:42,733
Be straight with me. About tomorrow...

526
00:29:43,651 --> 00:29:46,821
What do you think the success rate
of this operation is?

527
00:29:50,908 --> 00:29:52,827
If we're lucky...

528
00:29:55,246 --> 00:29:57,206
- About 50%?
- Darn it!

529
00:29:57,331 --> 00:30:00,834
Our lives are on the line,
and you say we only have a 50-50 chance?

530
00:30:00,835 --> 00:30:02,545
And that's me being generous.

531
00:30:17,518 --> 00:30:19,187
You know, when I was an agent

532
00:30:21,522 --> 00:30:23,733
I made it a point
not to think about failing

533
00:30:24,859 --> 00:30:27,278
before life-or-death operations.

534
00:30:27,820 --> 00:30:29,237
Instead...

535
00:30:29,238 --> 00:30:30,948
I'd think about what I'd do
after I succeeded.

536
00:30:31,824 --> 00:30:34,160
I just tried to think
as positively as I could.

537
00:30:34,785 --> 00:30:39,456
Surprisingly, that actually
helps the operation succeed.

538
00:30:39,457 --> 00:30:41,166
Look at you.

539
00:30:41,167 --> 00:30:43,336
As if you're the only one
who's ever been on operations.

540
00:30:44,337 --> 00:30:46,297
If this operation succeeds

541
00:30:48,382 --> 00:30:49,799
I'm going to watch a movie.

542
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:51,259
Not that anyone asked.

543
00:30:51,260 --> 00:30:53,429
- A movie?
- Yes, a movie.

544
00:30:54,472 --> 00:30:56,766
That Chow Yunfat movie I never got to see.

545
00:30:57,141 --> 00:30:59,936
This time, I'm going to make sure
we watch it together.

546
00:31:01,020 --> 00:31:03,855
You make it out alive
and all you want to do is watch a movie?

547
00:31:03,856 --> 00:31:06,858
What's wrong with a movie?
What grand plan do you have?

548
00:31:06,859 --> 00:31:07,902
Me?

549
00:31:08,694 --> 00:31:10,571
When I get the diamonds

550
00:31:11,614 --> 00:31:13,324
I'm going to take Nam-il to Monaco.

551
00:31:14,784 --> 00:31:18,621
Maybe if he sees another part of the world
and get some experience

552
00:31:19,330 --> 00:31:20,872
he'll finally grow up.

553
00:31:20,873 --> 00:31:22,874
Oh, what? Your plan's no better.

554
00:31:22,875 --> 00:31:25,544
So your grand plan
is to go on a family vacation?

555
00:31:26,796 --> 00:31:27,964
Jeong Ho-myeong.

556
00:31:28,256 --> 00:31:29,590
What about you? Any plans?

557
00:31:30,216 --> 00:31:31,217
Well, I...

558
00:31:32,843 --> 00:31:34,053
It's nothing special.

559
00:31:34,553 --> 00:31:35,596
I just...

560
00:31:37,056 --> 00:31:39,600
want to get a picture
to hang at the restaurant.

561
00:31:41,435 --> 00:31:44,522
To commemorate
the rest of my life and a fresh start.

562
00:31:45,982 --> 00:31:47,275
With the whole family.

563
00:31:52,488 --> 00:31:57,702
Do you think we can really
start over our lives after this job?

564
00:31:58,577 --> 00:32:00,120
What's stopping us?

565
00:32:00,121 --> 00:32:01,664
We're only halfway through life.

566
00:32:02,581 --> 00:32:03,958
We'll have to fight
for the other half of our lives

567
00:32:05,543 --> 00:32:07,670
with everything we've got.

568
00:32:09,422 --> 00:32:11,048
You better give me the diamonds
once we succeed.

569
00:32:40,703 --> 00:32:42,163
CANDIDATE NO. 2, HAN GYEONG-WOOK

570
00:32:50,087 --> 00:32:51,630
This is the intel Ri Chol Jin secured.

571
00:32:54,508 --> 00:32:57,302
I checked the attached audio file

572
00:32:57,303 --> 00:32:59,679
and it's certain Chairman Do
and Hwang Hwa-san betrayed us.

573
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:02,350
They're all being a pain
right before the big day.

574
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:06,603
I'll deal with them
once the election is over.

575
00:33:06,604 --> 00:33:08,772
Tell Ri Chol Jin to keep an eye on them.

576
00:33:08,773 --> 00:33:10,316
But sir...

577
00:33:11,150 --> 00:33:13,736
We haven't been able to contact
Ri Chol Jin since yesterday.

578
00:33:16,322 --> 00:33:17,405
Yes, hello!

579
00:33:17,406 --> 00:33:19,657
I'm Candidate Number Two. Yes, thank you.

580
00:33:19,658 --> 00:33:22,994
- Number Two! Yes, I'm Han Gyeong-wook!
- Number Two!

581
00:33:22,995 --> 00:33:24,579
Thank you.

582
00:33:24,580 --> 00:33:28,000
- Sir, can we get a picture?
- Of course, go ahead. There.

583
00:33:28,876 --> 00:33:32,088
Number Two! Yes, thank you.

584
00:33:33,255 --> 00:33:35,132
- Number Two!
- Number Two.

585
00:33:49,980 --> 00:33:52,191
What's wrong?
You look like you've seen a ghost.

586
00:33:53,359 --> 00:33:54,402
It's nothing.

587
00:33:59,115 --> 00:34:00,199
I actually...

588
00:34:00,699 --> 00:34:02,659
I got an urgent call from headquarters.

589
00:34:02,660 --> 00:34:03,993
Sir, why don't you take a break?

590
00:34:03,994 --> 00:34:06,037
In the middle of campaigning?

591
00:34:06,038 --> 00:34:07,832
- Just go and hurry back.
- Okay.

592
00:34:35,025 --> 00:34:36,985
Are you sure you should be stepping away?

593
00:34:36,985 --> 00:34:38,696
The election is right around the corner.

594
00:34:39,572 --> 00:34:41,364
You should be out there
meeting the voters.

595
00:34:48,289 --> 00:34:49,540
Seeing your face

596
00:34:50,916 --> 00:34:53,168
smiling so warmly like that

597
00:34:53,752 --> 00:34:55,838
I've realized that a man's greed

598
00:34:56,839 --> 00:34:58,340
is such a frightening thing.

599
00:34:58,883 --> 00:35:00,676
Have you completely lost your mind?

600
00:35:02,219 --> 00:35:04,554
How dare you just walk right up to me?

601
00:35:04,555 --> 00:35:07,223
You also came to the restaurant
to check on me.

602
00:35:07,224 --> 00:35:11,395
So I thought that as your junior,
I should pay you a visit.

603
00:35:11,979 --> 00:35:13,271
What are you up to?

604
00:35:13,272 --> 00:35:14,773
Up to?

605
00:35:15,024 --> 00:35:18,277
I came with the purest of intentions.
To see you one last time.

606
00:35:19,403 --> 00:35:23,240
It will be hard to see you
once you're arrested, after all.

607
00:35:25,326 --> 00:35:26,869
Don't bluff.

608
00:35:27,495 --> 00:35:29,371
The package is encrypted.

609
00:35:29,955 --> 00:35:31,289
Do you think I don't know that?

610
00:35:31,290 --> 00:35:32,291
Don't tell me...

611
00:35:32,958 --> 00:35:34,543
You still don't know.

612
00:35:35,628 --> 00:35:38,547
Oh, you must be too busy
with the campaign to watch the news.

613
00:35:39,048 --> 00:35:42,092
Watch the news.
I think you'll find it very interesting.

614
00:35:43,344 --> 00:35:44,845
I should go watch it myself.

615
00:35:45,221 --> 00:35:46,222
Well then, sir.

616
00:35:47,014 --> 00:35:48,681
I doubt we'll be seeing each other again

617
00:35:48,682 --> 00:35:51,936
but I hope you stay healthy and live long
to pay for your crimes.

618
00:36:04,114 --> 00:36:05,365
Are you all right, sir?

619
00:36:05,366 --> 00:36:06,699
Follow him quietly.

620
00:36:06,700 --> 00:36:08,827
Make sure to find out where he's going.

621
00:36:09,662 --> 00:36:10,663
Yes, sir.

622
00:36:16,043 --> 00:36:17,877
One of the suspects

623
00:36:17,878 --> 00:36:20,004
is from North Korea's
Ministry of People's Armed Forces

624
00:36:20,005 --> 00:36:22,632
and has been identified
as Major Ri Chol Jin

625
00:36:22,633 --> 00:36:25,885
who infiltrated the country
to gather state secrets

626
00:36:25,886 --> 00:36:28,055
and is accused of
threatening national security.

627
00:36:28,889 --> 00:36:31,058
We have secured a statement

628
00:36:31,392 --> 00:36:33,142
indicating that former Assemblyman
Han Gyeong-wook

629
00:36:33,143 --> 00:36:34,852
currently a candidate for Mayor of Imcheon

630
00:36:34,853 --> 00:36:36,772
is the likely mastermind behind this case.

631
00:36:37,815 --> 00:36:39,857
With the mayoral election
just around the corner

632
00:36:39,858 --> 00:36:42,111
to have to announce
such a sensitive matter...

633
00:36:42,570 --> 00:36:44,572
I sincerely regret it.

634
00:36:44,905 --> 00:36:47,950
However, as this is an urgent matter
threatening national security

635
00:36:49,285 --> 00:36:53,788
we at the prosecution,
without any political bias or agenda

636
00:36:53,789 --> 00:36:55,540
and with pure intentions

637
00:36:55,541 --> 00:36:58,711
will thoroughly and clearly uncover
the truth of this case.

638
00:36:58,836 --> 00:37:01,630
We promise this
to the people of the nation.

639
00:37:03,591 --> 00:37:05,551
I'm sending you
the location of the package.

640
00:37:06,176 --> 00:37:07,177
I'll see you there.

641
00:37:12,850 --> 00:37:13,851
Good work.

642
00:37:17,187 --> 00:37:18,938
Are you sure you provoked Han Gyeong-wook?

643
00:37:18,939 --> 00:37:21,191
I leaked our location on purpose.

644
00:37:23,527 --> 00:37:26,488
All right. Let's start getting ready.

645
00:37:29,158 --> 00:37:30,283
This is a meaningful day

646
00:37:30,284 --> 00:37:33,703
where we finish the operation
that failed ten years ago.

647
00:37:33,704 --> 00:37:35,581
We can't show up
looking like this, can we?

648
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:45,424
For just today, let's go back
to that day ten years ago.

649
00:37:48,677 --> 00:37:49,845
It's not a skirt, is it?

650
00:37:53,515 --> 00:37:55,892
I've confirmed their location.

651
00:37:55,893 --> 00:37:57,436
They're at Yeongseon Resort.

652
00:38:01,523 --> 00:38:02,524
And the rangers?

653
00:38:02,858 --> 00:38:04,359
They're ready.

654
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:06,403
Our little lambs have also arrived.

655
00:38:08,113 --> 00:38:11,032
Chairman, I know you're aware of this.

656
00:38:11,033 --> 00:38:13,452
But we can't let our guard down,
especially now.

657
00:38:13,577 --> 00:38:16,121
Those men are no ordinary guys.

658
00:38:17,414 --> 00:38:22,002
We need to prepare perfectly
and strike once, decisively.

659
00:38:22,336 --> 00:38:25,839
I'm more of an expert in these matters
than you are, Chairman Do.

660
00:38:26,924 --> 00:38:29,510
Before they even know what hit them

661
00:38:30,219 --> 00:38:32,638
it'll all be over.

662
00:38:34,473 --> 00:38:35,516
About Prosecutor Gang...

663
00:38:36,684 --> 00:38:38,977
Weren't you supposed to take care of her?

664
00:38:39,186 --> 00:38:43,023
Well, we tried to, but she was with...

665
00:38:44,108 --> 00:38:47,193
Anyway, just give me more time.

666
00:38:47,194 --> 00:38:49,570
I'll do everything I can
to block the warrant.

667
00:38:49,571 --> 00:38:51,198
"Do everything you can"?

668
00:38:51,949 --> 00:38:53,492
Are you kidding me right now?

669
00:38:54,702 --> 00:38:56,203
It's your job to block it no matter what.

670
00:38:57,287 --> 00:39:00,541
If you can't,
I'm not the only one going down.

671
00:39:01,417 --> 00:39:03,711
Are you threatening me?

672
00:39:05,003 --> 00:39:06,630
Of course I am.

673
00:39:07,464 --> 00:39:09,090
I can't give you much time.

674
00:39:09,091 --> 00:39:11,885
Handle it by the end of the day.
No matter what.

675
00:39:14,263 --> 00:39:16,723
Gosh, what is happening?

676
00:39:16,724 --> 00:39:17,850
Is this part of your campaign?

677
00:39:18,851 --> 00:39:20,644
Or did you really do something?

678
00:39:21,353 --> 00:39:24,355
You've dragged North Korea into this
and ruined my image.

679
00:39:24,356 --> 00:39:25,690
How are you going to take responsibility?

680
00:39:25,691 --> 00:39:27,693
Will you please be quiet?

681
00:39:27,985 --> 00:39:29,569
I'm thinking.

682
00:39:29,570 --> 00:39:30,654
What?

683
00:39:31,321 --> 00:39:32,739
Hey, Han Gyeong-wook.

684
00:39:32,740 --> 00:39:34,742
How dare you look at me like that?

685
00:39:35,617 --> 00:39:38,077
You're just a commie punk
who consorts with North Koreans.

686
00:39:38,078 --> 00:39:39,621
What do you have to be so smug about?

687
00:39:46,712 --> 00:39:48,672
Assemblyman Han, what are you doing?

688
00:39:49,631 --> 00:39:51,591
Shut your damn mouth.

689
00:39:51,592 --> 00:39:52,593
Hey, Kim Jung-hyeok.

690
00:39:53,761 --> 00:39:57,054
I at least made some money
consorting with North Koreans.

691
00:39:57,055 --> 00:40:00,100
What did you get from messing around
with some young chick?

692
00:40:00,601 --> 00:40:03,770
Do your kids know
that you gave her a whole building?

693
00:40:03,771 --> 00:40:04,854
What?

694
00:40:04,855 --> 00:40:07,608
Pictures of you fooling around with a girl
young enough to be your daughter.

695
00:40:08,192 --> 00:40:10,986
It'd be easy to plaster them
all over the internet.

696
00:40:11,445 --> 00:40:12,529
So...

697
00:40:12,863 --> 00:40:16,033
Do you want me to turn you
into a notorious adulterer right now?

698
00:40:16,283 --> 00:40:18,952
Adulterer? Hey, you right now...

699
00:40:19,161 --> 00:40:20,496
Hey, Kim Jung-hyeok.

700
00:40:21,580 --> 00:40:23,289
If I really wanted to

701
00:40:23,290 --> 00:40:27,503
it'd be easy for me
to make you disappear without a trace.

702
00:40:28,253 --> 00:40:30,129
So if you don't want to die

703
00:40:30,130 --> 00:40:33,217
mobilize the prosecutors, the media,
everything you've got and stop this.

704
00:40:33,383 --> 00:40:34,802
Do you understand me?

705
00:40:36,011 --> 00:40:37,095
Yes, I do.

706
00:40:57,032 --> 00:40:58,200
Get a move on!

707
00:41:20,138 --> 00:41:21,265
There's no one here.

708
00:41:22,266 --> 00:41:25,227
You don't think
they caught on and ran away?

709
00:41:25,477 --> 00:41:27,271
The number you have dialed
is unavailable...

710
00:41:41,535 --> 00:41:43,871
Who says we ran away?

711
00:41:46,415 --> 00:41:48,040
We've been waiting for you.

712
00:41:48,041 --> 00:41:49,877
Hi!

713
00:41:51,003 --> 00:41:52,379
Gosh, so many of you came.

714
00:41:54,089 --> 00:41:55,299
Boss.

715
00:41:57,342 --> 00:41:58,551
Wow...

716
00:41:58,552 --> 00:41:59,803
Chairman.

717
00:42:00,012 --> 00:42:02,680
What exactly is going on here?

718
00:42:02,681 --> 00:42:04,474
Gang Beom-ryong, Ma Gong-bok.

719
00:42:05,225 --> 00:42:07,436
How dare you two betray me?

720
00:42:09,897 --> 00:42:12,148
Do you have any right to say that, Boss?

721
00:42:12,149 --> 00:42:13,191
What?

722
00:42:14,026 --> 00:42:16,068
You said you'd just be taking the package.

723
00:42:16,069 --> 00:42:17,946
But you brought all your lackeys with you.

724
00:42:19,239 --> 00:42:22,700
Weren't you planning to get rid of
Ma Gong-bok and Gang Beom-ryong

725
00:42:22,701 --> 00:42:24,118
once you found the package?

726
00:42:24,119 --> 00:42:25,620
You NIS punk!

727
00:42:25,621 --> 00:42:27,122
Wait, Chairman.

728
00:42:27,623 --> 00:42:29,082
Calm down.

729
00:42:29,625 --> 00:42:31,460
All right, everyone.

730
00:42:31,752 --> 00:42:34,254
Let's all calm down
and have a little talk, shall we?

731
00:42:34,963 --> 00:42:39,718
I heard roughly what happened
ten years ago, so I get it.

732
00:42:40,052 --> 00:42:42,137
So the bottom line is...

733
00:42:42,763 --> 00:42:45,265
You want to get revenge
on Han Gyeong-wook, right?

734
00:42:46,183 --> 00:42:49,394
That's right. We are the same, okay?

735
00:42:49,645 --> 00:42:52,898
We have a score to settle
with Han Gyeong-wook, too. Okay?

736
00:42:53,065 --> 00:42:54,399
Hey, foreigner.

737
00:42:55,400 --> 00:42:56,568
So what are you going to do?

738
00:42:57,861 --> 00:42:59,654
Look, either way

739
00:42:59,655 --> 00:43:01,530
just the four of you aren't big enough

740
00:43:01,531 --> 00:43:03,825
to take on Han Gyeong-wook, are you?

741
00:43:04,952 --> 00:43:06,869
So let's not waste our energy
fighting each other.

742
00:43:06,870 --> 00:43:08,621
Give us the package.

743
00:43:08,622 --> 00:43:09,997
In return

744
00:43:09,998 --> 00:43:13,417
we'll make sure you get your revenge.

745
00:43:13,418 --> 00:43:14,419
Oh, really?

746
00:43:19,841 --> 00:43:21,468
Deputy Director Han,
what are you doing here?

747
00:43:21,927 --> 00:43:23,553
Deputy Director Han.

748
00:43:24,930 --> 00:43:26,181
Hyeon-tae.

749
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:27,766
Do Hyeon-tae.

750
00:43:28,934 --> 00:43:31,853
I've told you before, haven't I?

751
00:43:32,104 --> 00:43:34,564
Know your place and don't cross the line.

752
00:43:35,565 --> 00:43:36,941
Chairman Hwang.

753
00:43:36,942 --> 00:43:39,695
I thought you were a man of sound judgment

754
00:43:40,153 --> 00:43:41,947
but it seems I was mistaken about you.

755
00:43:42,364 --> 00:43:43,656
I'm very disappointed.

756
00:43:43,657 --> 00:43:45,575
Don't give me that.

757
00:43:46,451 --> 00:43:50,330
I think you're the one
who needs to know your place.

758
00:43:51,081 --> 00:43:53,457
- What?
- Did you think

759
00:43:53,458 --> 00:43:56,294
we'd come this far without preparing
for a situation like this?

760
00:44:08,015 --> 00:44:09,474
Okay, fine.

761
00:44:10,934 --> 00:44:13,186
I know you're all upset with me.

762
00:44:14,688 --> 00:44:15,731
But still...

763
00:44:17,065 --> 00:44:18,984
We shouldn't be fighting
amongst ourselves.

764
00:44:22,821 --> 00:44:25,699
That's just what he wants.

765
00:44:27,367 --> 00:44:28,493
Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong.

766
00:44:29,745 --> 00:44:34,041
I guess your plan
was to gather us here, make us fight

767
00:44:34,249 --> 00:44:37,961
and watch us destroy each other,
or something like that.

768
00:44:38,837 --> 00:44:40,296
But unfortunately for you

769
00:44:40,297 --> 00:44:44,092
I have no intention of fighting these two.

770
00:44:46,845 --> 00:44:48,221
What do you say?

771
00:44:48,680 --> 00:44:50,849
Rather than playing right into his hands

772
00:44:51,767 --> 00:44:55,771
let's deal with them first
and then have a calm discussion.

773
00:44:57,397 --> 00:44:58,522
What kind of discussion?

774
00:44:58,523 --> 00:44:59,524
Well...

775
00:45:00,275 --> 00:45:03,987
Like redistributing the profits
from the Yeongseon Island Project.

776
00:45:04,905 --> 00:45:08,283
There's plenty of room for negotiation,
don't you think?

777
00:45:09,201 --> 00:45:10,535
You believe that?

778
00:45:12,454 --> 00:45:15,123
You think Han Gyeong-wook
would ever negotiate with traitors?

779
00:45:27,344 --> 00:45:28,803
Fine.

780
00:45:28,804 --> 00:45:30,096
First...

781
00:45:30,097 --> 00:45:33,683
Let's deal with the traitor Judas.

782
00:45:37,270 --> 00:45:38,271
Ho-myeong.

783
00:45:39,231 --> 00:45:41,274
As your senior,
this is my final act of mercy.

784
00:45:42,275 --> 00:45:45,278
Hand over the package and back off.

785
00:45:45,737 --> 00:45:48,907
Then I'll let you live.

786
00:45:55,789 --> 00:45:57,290
And if I refuse?

787
00:46:01,044 --> 00:46:02,129
What are you all waiting for?

788
00:46:26,111 --> 00:46:27,237
Prosecutor.

789
00:46:29,781 --> 00:46:32,159
Prosecutor, we have a huge problem.
All the warrants were denied.

790
00:46:32,993 --> 00:46:33,994
Darn it.

791
00:46:34,911 --> 00:46:35,996
Denied, you say.

792
00:46:36,288 --> 00:46:39,206
It looks like the Chief Prosecutor
pulled some strings.

793
00:46:39,207 --> 00:46:40,375
What do we do?

794
00:47:14,743 --> 00:47:16,703
Oh, Prosecutor Gang.

795
00:47:17,162 --> 00:47:20,040
I was just about to send for you.
Perfect timing.

796
00:47:28,006 --> 00:47:29,131
What's going on?

797
00:47:29,132 --> 00:47:30,926
I saw your press conference.

798
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:57,577
I saw the press conference as well.

799
00:47:59,454 --> 00:48:03,541
Compared to how you look on TV,
you're much prettier in person.

800
00:48:05,460 --> 00:48:06,877
No matter how I look at it

801
00:48:06,878 --> 00:48:10,130
you don't look like someone
who catches spies.

802
00:48:10,131 --> 00:48:11,215
Come on.

803
00:48:11,216 --> 00:48:14,135
They're not really spies, are they?

804
00:48:15,095 --> 00:48:19,348
Our Prosecutor Gang here
just wanted a moment in the spotlight

805
00:48:19,349 --> 00:48:21,476
and went overboard.

806
00:48:22,269 --> 00:48:23,520
Isn't that right, Prosecutor Gang?

807
00:48:30,986 --> 00:48:32,612
- Are you all right?
- No.

808
00:49:10,567 --> 00:49:12,986
Chief Prosecutor, do you have no shame?

809
00:49:13,778 --> 00:49:15,738
I'm giving you one last chance.

810
00:49:15,739 --> 00:49:16,740
The warrants.

811
00:49:17,365 --> 00:49:19,034
Process them according to procedure.

812
00:49:29,210 --> 00:49:33,673
You know very well
who these guys are, don't you?

813
00:49:35,467 --> 00:49:37,302
Make the right call. Got it?

814
00:49:37,677 --> 00:49:40,888
Depending on the call you make here

815
00:49:40,889 --> 00:49:44,183
you could end up becoming
a crooked prosecutor

816
00:49:44,184 --> 00:49:46,436
covering for gangsters and spies.

817
00:49:47,062 --> 00:49:50,857
A prosecutor colluding
with gangsters and North Korea.

818
00:49:52,233 --> 00:49:54,068
When the lower ranks are so corrupt

819
00:49:54,069 --> 00:49:56,446
it must be difficult for you at the top.

820
00:49:58,073 --> 00:50:00,033
It's truly embarrassing.

821
00:50:00,575 --> 00:50:03,495
We'll have to clean house soon.

822
00:50:19,719 --> 00:50:21,012
Boss!

823
00:50:34,442 --> 00:50:35,819
Gong-bok!

824
00:50:36,069 --> 00:50:37,278
Aren't you leaving?

825
00:50:38,405 --> 00:50:39,781
Are you just going to stand there?

826
00:50:40,615 --> 00:50:42,450
But it feels like such a shame to leave.

827
00:50:43,535 --> 00:50:45,495
And there are some people
I'd like you to meet.

828
00:50:46,121 --> 00:50:47,122
What?

829
00:50:47,539 --> 00:50:48,706
Come on in.

830
00:50:51,793 --> 00:50:52,794
Hello, sir.

831
00:50:53,628 --> 00:50:55,839
Wait... You!

832
00:50:56,673 --> 00:50:58,425
Do you know them?

833
00:50:59,134 --> 00:51:00,135
Then again...

834
00:51:01,136 --> 00:51:03,554
You must know them
to make calls like this.

835
00:51:03,555 --> 00:51:06,474
I approved Prosecutor Gang's leave
on purpose.

836
00:51:06,975 --> 00:51:10,478
You know things got out of hand last time
because you lost her, right?

837
00:51:10,770 --> 00:51:13,857
This time, you're not tailing her.
You're eliminating her.

838
00:51:14,149 --> 00:51:15,650
You absolutely cannot make any mistakes.

839
00:51:21,781 --> 00:51:22,782
Make the right call.

840
00:51:24,284 --> 00:51:25,368
You two.

841
00:51:26,161 --> 00:51:29,914
He's a man who ordered the murder
of a prosecutor of the Republic of Korea.

842
00:51:30,748 --> 00:51:32,374
If you don't want to
get cleaned out with him

843
00:51:32,375 --> 00:51:34,002
choose your next step wisely.

844
00:52:02,447 --> 00:52:03,448
Boss!

845
00:52:10,371 --> 00:52:11,831
Sorry.

846
00:52:12,957 --> 00:52:14,125
We'll talk later.

847
00:52:14,542 --> 00:52:16,336
You've got a really hard head.

848
00:52:40,652 --> 00:52:41,902
You can't manage without me, can you?

849
00:52:41,903 --> 00:52:43,404
No, we were doing just fine!

850
00:52:45,365 --> 00:52:48,576
Gosh, how can I trust you guys
with a guerrilla operation?

851
00:53:23,361 --> 00:53:25,196
Let's wrap this up.

852
00:53:26,531 --> 00:53:28,157
This is getting boring.

853
00:53:44,215 --> 00:53:45,258
Mr. Geum.

854
00:53:46,050 --> 00:53:47,634
Yoo In-gu...

855
00:53:47,635 --> 00:53:49,845
All my enemies have gathered here.

856
00:53:49,846 --> 00:53:52,222
Gosh, that gangster bastard.

857
00:53:52,223 --> 00:53:54,726
Oh, Deputy Director Han. And the big boss.

858
00:53:55,310 --> 00:53:57,520
- That sly fox, Chairman Do.
- Darn it.

859
00:53:59,230 --> 00:54:01,774
The martial arts master
and even Gang Beom-ryong.

860
00:54:02,358 --> 00:54:04,694
This is perfect. Saves me the trouble
of hunting you all down.

861
00:54:04,819 --> 00:54:06,862
That leech, Yoo In-gu.

862
00:54:06,863 --> 00:54:09,782
What's going on?
Why'd you bring such scrawny guys?

863
00:54:10,325 --> 00:54:12,660
If they join in,
we might actually be in trouble.

864
00:54:14,621 --> 00:54:15,663
Hey, In-gu.

865
00:54:16,873 --> 00:54:18,041
So who should we strike first?

866
00:54:18,374 --> 00:54:19,542
Who first...

867
00:54:20,293 --> 00:54:21,752
Can't we just strike all at once?

868
00:54:21,753 --> 00:54:24,004
Hey, we've only got two hands.
How would we hit them all at once?

869
00:54:24,005 --> 00:54:25,672
You have to tell us the order.

870
00:54:25,673 --> 00:54:26,883
Okay.

871
00:54:29,719 --> 00:54:32,512
Hey, Yoo In-gu,
what's there to think about?

872
00:54:32,513 --> 00:54:34,306
Those are the guys
who busted your drug deal.

873
00:54:34,307 --> 00:54:35,891
You should be going after them.

874
00:54:35,892 --> 00:54:38,477
That one first. That scumbag!

875
00:54:38,478 --> 00:54:39,479
Me?

876
00:54:40,104 --> 00:54:41,688
Are you crazy?

877
00:54:41,689 --> 00:54:44,108
They're the ones
who busted the deal. Not me.

878
00:54:44,233 --> 00:54:45,442
That's rich.

879
00:54:45,443 --> 00:54:47,444
I can't stand it when
that fake Yankee speaks English.

880
00:54:47,445 --> 00:54:49,196
- Get him first.
- What?

881
00:54:49,197 --> 00:54:51,157
That stupid punk first. Quickly!

882
00:54:52,575 --> 00:54:53,618
Let's get you out of here, sir.

883
00:54:57,538 --> 00:54:58,790
What's the plan?

884
00:54:59,957 --> 00:55:01,541
Get Gong-bok out of here.

885
00:55:01,542 --> 00:55:03,711
- Let's go!
- Go where?

886
00:55:36,786 --> 00:55:37,787
Why, you...

887
00:55:47,046 --> 00:55:48,172
What the hell?

888
00:55:55,555 --> 00:55:57,306
What are you doing? Finish them quickly.

889
00:55:58,015 --> 00:55:59,016
Let's go.

890
00:56:00,727 --> 00:56:01,728
Slow down.

891
00:56:03,938 --> 00:56:05,690
- Hurry up, come on!
- Okay.

892
00:56:06,774 --> 00:56:07,775
Are you okay?

893
00:56:28,921 --> 00:56:30,005
Hey, Yoo In-gu.

894
00:56:30,006 --> 00:56:31,174
Yes, sir?

895
00:56:31,632 --> 00:56:33,258
Get lost if you don't want to die.

896
00:56:33,259 --> 00:56:34,260
Yes, sir.

897
00:56:40,641 --> 00:56:42,018
Jeong Ho-myeong.

898
00:56:42,393 --> 00:56:43,895
Hand the package over.

899
00:56:44,771 --> 00:56:46,063
If you're pulling a gun

900
00:56:47,231 --> 00:56:48,775
this is going to get
a lot more complicated.

901
00:56:50,359 --> 00:56:53,905
As long as I can get out of here,
cleaning this up will be easy.

902
00:57:00,286 --> 00:57:01,537
I'll say this one last time.

903
00:57:03,164 --> 00:57:04,582
Hand over the package!

904
00:57:33,486 --> 00:57:34,904
All right, let's go.

905
00:57:35,905 --> 00:57:36,906
Still...

906
00:57:37,949 --> 00:57:40,117
I should at least pay you
for the package, right?

907
00:58:52,815 --> 00:58:54,025
What?

908
00:58:55,943 --> 00:58:57,986
- It hurts.
- What?

909
00:58:57,987 --> 00:58:59,947
- Can you hear us?
- Mr. Jeong!

910
00:59:00,448 --> 00:59:02,198
It hurts.

911
00:59:02,199 --> 00:59:03,784
- I'll call an ambulance.
- Okay.

912
00:59:05,745 --> 00:59:06,870
Hey, snap out of it. Are you okay?

913
00:59:06,871 --> 00:59:08,539
It hurts.

914
00:59:11,083 --> 00:59:12,876
Hey, wait. It hurts so much.

915
00:59:12,877 --> 00:59:14,628
Of course it hurts, you idiot.
You got shot.

916
00:59:14,629 --> 00:59:16,464
No, my hand...

917
00:59:16,839 --> 00:59:18,466
It hurts. My hand.

918
00:59:22,053 --> 00:59:23,553
Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong.

919
00:59:23,554 --> 00:59:24,805
Are you okay?

920
00:59:26,390 --> 00:59:29,351
Just help me up.

921
00:59:29,352 --> 00:59:31,270
Why would you get up after getting shot?

922
00:59:31,437 --> 00:59:33,605
- Hurry up. Quick.
- He seems okay. Let's help him up.

923
00:59:33,606 --> 00:59:35,107
Just hurry up and help me up.

924
00:59:38,027 --> 00:59:40,279
- It hurts.
- One, two, three!

925
00:59:42,990 --> 00:59:44,450
It hurts.

926
00:59:44,575 --> 00:59:45,576
It hurts.

927
00:59:46,827 --> 00:59:49,080
- Jeez, seriously.
- Gosh, he's heavy.

928
00:59:49,997 --> 00:59:51,873
It hurts, really.

929
00:59:51,874 --> 00:59:53,875
I haven't been shot in a while.
This really hurts.

930
00:59:53,876 --> 00:59:56,086
- Gosh, you're such an idiot.
- I'm dying.

931
00:59:56,087 --> 00:59:57,545
Getting yourself stabbed...

932
00:59:57,546 --> 00:59:58,797
Hey, I got shot.

933
00:59:58,798 --> 01:00:00,633
- Oh, right. You got shot.
- What do you mean, stabbed?

934
01:00:01,717 --> 01:00:03,886
Hey, you two have really lost your touch.

935
01:00:04,679 --> 01:00:05,887
Lost our touch?

936
01:00:05,888 --> 01:00:08,223
Hey, I had to help
you two pathetic weaklings out.

937
01:00:08,224 --> 01:00:10,392
Hey, I took care of everyone today.
I finished them all.

938
01:00:10,393 --> 01:00:11,936
If it weren't for me,
you both would be dead.

939
01:00:12,895 --> 01:00:14,896
I took out 42 guys today.

940
01:00:14,897 --> 01:00:16,940
Hey, you hit me in the back of the head
on purpose earlier, didn't you?

941
01:00:16,941 --> 01:00:19,860
I didn't do it on purpose,
but your head is really hard.

942
01:00:21,779 --> 01:00:23,697
No. Hey, be gentle.

943
01:00:23,698 --> 01:00:25,323
- I told you it hurts!
- Come on!

944
01:00:25,324 --> 01:00:26,742
- Then I'll let go, okay?
- It's so bad.

945
01:00:43,259 --> 01:00:44,301
What?

946
01:00:45,094 --> 01:00:46,345
What's this?

947
01:00:46,887 --> 01:00:48,013
Earth Defense Force!

948
01:00:48,014 --> 01:00:49,557
- Masked Racer!
- Masked Racer!

949
01:01:01,652 --> 01:01:04,530
Jeong Ho-myeong, that damn bastard!

950
01:01:10,244 --> 01:01:14,664
Reporting on the national security case
that shook the last mayoral election

951
01:01:14,665 --> 01:01:16,833
involving Candidate Han Gyeong-wook.

952
01:01:16,834 --> 01:01:20,128
According to the prosecution's recent
interim investigation announcement

953
01:01:20,129 --> 01:01:22,881
mayoral candidate Han Gyeong-wook
colluded with Major Ri Chol Jin

954
01:01:22,882 --> 01:01:24,841
of North Korea's
Ministry of People's Armed Forces

955
01:01:24,842 --> 01:01:27,343
and was not only involved in
drug trafficking ten years ago

956
01:01:27,344 --> 01:01:29,763
but also allegations that he tried to
hand Yeongseon Island over

957
01:01:29,764 --> 01:01:33,683
to an overseas criminal organization
are being repeatedly confirmed as true.

958
01:01:33,684 --> 01:01:36,227
Candidate Han Gyeong-wook
is reportedly facing trial today

959
01:01:36,228 --> 01:01:39,272
for multiple counts of murder
and solicitation of murder.

960
01:01:39,273 --> 01:01:43,109
While authorities focus on
tracking the candidate's past activities

961
01:01:43,110 --> 01:01:44,986
they are also expanding the investigation

962
01:01:44,987 --> 01:01:47,238
to the entire Yeongseon Island
development project

963
01:01:47,239 --> 01:01:49,657
that he had put forward
as a campaign pledge.

964
01:01:49,658 --> 01:01:52,035
In particular, as this investigation
confirms the involvement

965
01:01:52,036 --> 01:01:55,580
of not only domestic groups
but also overseas criminal networks

966
01:01:55,581 --> 01:01:59,709
it is reported to have grown
beyond a single incident

967
01:01:59,710 --> 01:02:02,003
into a wide-ranging joint investigation.

968
01:02:02,004 --> 01:02:04,339
As a result,
getting to the bottom of the case

969
01:02:04,340 --> 01:02:06,633
is expected to take
a considerable amount of time

970
01:02:06,634 --> 01:02:08,551
and it is also being suggested

971
01:02:08,552 --> 01:02:12,097
that more evidence of crimes
may be revealed in stages.

972
01:02:12,098 --> 01:02:13,348
In other news

973
01:02:13,349 --> 01:02:16,476
at an orphanage facility,
a mysterious donor

974
01:02:16,477 --> 01:02:20,188
reportedly left behind valuable diamonds

975
01:02:20,189 --> 01:02:23,066
touching the hearts
of the local community.

976
01:02:23,067 --> 01:02:26,361
The diamonds
were discovered in a small box

977
01:02:26,362 --> 01:02:28,613
that had been left
in front of the orphanage office.

978
01:02:28,614 --> 01:02:30,657
A short, handwritten note left with it

979
01:02:30,658 --> 01:02:32,742
reportedly only contained the message

980
01:02:32,743 --> 01:02:34,787
"Please use this for the children."

981
01:02:41,544 --> 01:02:42,795
- We apologize.
- We apologize.

982
01:02:49,343 --> 01:02:53,639
Hey, let me get in the picture too!
Let's all take one together.

983
01:02:59,395 --> 01:03:00,478
- Get over here!
- Uncle!

984
01:03:00,479 --> 01:03:02,480
- Hurry up!
- Manager Bong, hurry up!

985
01:03:02,481 --> 01:03:03,773
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

986
01:03:03,774 --> 01:03:04,775
Okay.

987
01:03:10,489 --> 01:03:11,866
Let's take the picture.

988
01:03:17,997 --> 01:03:20,415
- Mr. Kim should be here by now.
- What are you all doing without me?

989
01:03:20,416 --> 01:03:21,499
Come on, hurry up!

990
01:03:21,500 --> 01:03:23,127
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

991
01:03:27,298 --> 01:03:29,842
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT
